@node play "The game: Installation/Playing"

                             Installation

  The installation is very simple, just place 'Tri_Q' where you
want on your hard drive, floppy disk, Ram Disk, etc. No other files
or Libraries are needed.

NOTE: As I am not sure of this game's 'behaviour' on a stock 68000
      Amiga. For now, until somebody confirms that Tri_Q runs fine
      on a 68000 machine, this game will require an Amiga with a
      68020 or faster processor... sorry!

                             How to play?

  To move a peg (a tile with a black and white circle), just click
on it with the mouse pointer and you click on the empty space (a
tile with a small dot) where you want to move the peg. You can only
move a peg 2 spaces horizontally or diagonally. If the move is
possible, the selected peg will go there.

  In 'Tri_Q' there are two ways to play:

  -The Normal game:   You jump over a @{b}peg@{ub} and that peg
                      will be removed. Try to remove all the pegs
                      until only one is left, preferably where the
                      empty space was located at the start.

  -The Inverted game: You jump over an @{b}empty space@{ub} and a
                      peg will appear there, just as if you would
                      play the normal game backward. Try to 'fill'
                      up the board until only one empty space is
                      left, preferably where the peg was located at
                      the start.

  When there are no possible moves, the game ends and Tri_Q
displays how many pegs (or empty spaces for the 'Inverted' game)
are remaining.

  Have fun!

OPTIONS

 -New Game:              Restarts the game.

 -About...:              Displays the informations about the game.

 -Normal/Inverted Game:  Toggles between the 'Normal' and the
                         'Inverted' game.

 -Gameboard: Mini...Big: Changes the game board size.

  You can quit the game by clicking on the main window's close
button or by pressing on the 'Esc' key.

